<h1 id="blank-stylesheet-import">Blank stylesheet import</h1>

<p>I simply have this stylesheet link in my header:</p>

<p><code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;link id="mainstyle" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/main.css" /&gt;</code></p>

<p>The 2 sidebars also have a similar link. Currently if you are using the dark theme</p>

<h1 id="style-sheet">Style sheet</h1>

<p>I use <a href="http://sass-lang.com">sass</a> to handle my style sheets, so I simply have the appropriate variables set up for the stylesheets. Sass generates the different themes for me.</p>

<p>My ‘Dark’ sass looks something like this right now:</p>

